{
  "texts": [
    "and in particular:",
    "We could go through the proof until the end, but you can now guess that it's essentially Chernoff bound + rearrangement of the terms.",
    "□ Clerico et al. (2022b) proposed a very clever use of such a PAC-Bayes bound that does not actually require to sample from ρ.",
    "They study a sequence (θ t) t=0,...,T obtained by gradient descent, with a random initialization θ 0.",
    "The prior π is taken as the distribution of θ 0, and ρ is defined implicitly as the distribution of θ T."
  ]
}